+## v6 Roadmap Scan
+
+The same four pattern groups used in the earlier court were applied to v6:
+
+```powershell
+rg -n -i "file[ -]?explorer|file[ -]?manager|FileExplorer|FileManager|dosya gezgini|dosya|explorer" source-snapshots/raw/pala-os-v6
+rg -n -i "settings|ayar|react-hook-form|shadcn|form" source-snapshots/raw/pala-os-v6
+rg -n -i "browser|tarayici|langchain|agent|tool" source-snapshots/raw/pala-os-v6
+rg -n -i "sigma|supabase|iframe|analytics|dashboard" source-snapshots/raw/pala-os-v6
+```
+
+## v6 Findings
+
+File explorer finding: no reusable Pala desktop file explorer component was found.
+
+Representative matches were general file/doc references and Windows Explorer launch language:
+
+- `plans/README.md`
+- `README.md` mentioning `launch.cmd` from Windows Explorer
+- `docs/v6-readonly-audit-report.md`
+- `docs/seed-skill-registry-contract.md`
+
+Settings/forms finding: v6 has a useful `form-sentry` evidence battalion concept in `src/evidence-battalions.js`, but no ready shadcn settings form implementation.
+
+AI browser finding: v6 has browser-adjacent infrastructure, including `PALA_OPEN_BROWSER`, local dashboard open behavior, MCP read-only tools, and tests around local HTTP dashboard APIs. It does not contain a browser tab action LangChain tool ready for direct v5 import.
+
+Sigma/Supabase/dashboard finding: v6 is valuable for dashboard-first operation, local MCP, benchmark panel, and evidence-driven UI language. It does not change the file explorer decision.
+
+## Updated Court Decision
+
+File explorer implementation status after v6 inclusion: `NOT_PRESENT_IN_SOURCES`
+
+Recommended next safe step remains:
+
+```text
+Create a new v0.dev/shadcn UI file explorer for pala-os-v5, then adapt it through the v5 evidence/report gate.
+```
+
+Updated allowed reuse:
+
+- Use v3/v4/v5 dashboard truth and evidence discipline as implementation constraints.
+- Use v6 dashboard-first and MCP/browser-open patterns as constraints for later AI browser and command-surface work.
+- Use Figma/v0.dev output as the primary source for the new file explorer UI.
+
+Updated blocked reuse:
+
+- Do not claim v6 contains a finished Pala OS file explorer.
+- Do not import local dirty v6 files unless the owner explicitly approves and a separate dirty-change court package is created.
+- Do not copy raw snapshot code into v5 without a separate court note and changed-files manifest.
