@@ -0,0 +1,96 @@
+# Pala OS V6
+
+Local-first Pala OS command center for Codex-style work.
+
+Current state: V6 is an executable local command-center foundation. It is not release-ready yet; the court intentionally returns `RELEASE_BLOCKED` until owner approval and required evidence exist.
+
+## What this is
+
+- A local dashboard first.
+- A machine-readable 60-standard policy engine.
+- A SQLite-backed evidence ledger.
+- A GitHub-aware control surface.
+- A no-fake-done command center.
+
+## Current inventory
+
+- Standards catalog: 60 total standards.
+- Policy split: 42 required standards and 18 recommended standards.
+- Current court status: 42 required standards blocked because evidence is missing.
+- Evidence battalions: 25 machine-readable evidence groups.
+- Source cards: 4 quarantined upstream lineage cards for `pala-os`, `pala-os-v3`, `pala-os-v4`, and `pala-os-v5`.
+- API endpoints: 12 local endpoints.
+- Committed source layout: 18 source modules, 2 utility scripts, 1 test file, 1 GitHub Actions workflow, 9 top-level docs, 3 agent contract docs, 1 schema doc, 1 Codex plugin manifest, 1 Dockerfile, 1 Compose file, 1 benchmark fixture, 1 court fixture, 1 plan, 1 prompt, and 1 skill registry.
+
+## Quick start
+
+```bash
+node src/cli.js bootstrap
+node src/cli.js up
+```
+
+On Windows, you can also double-click `launch.cmd` to bootstrap and open the deck.
+
+## Core commands
+
+- `sak init` or `sak bootstrap` - create `.pala`, seed the policy catalog, and initialize SQLite.
+- `sak up` - start the local dashboard and open it in the browser.
+- `sak status` - show the current summary.
+- `sak bak "<query>"` - generate a task-scoped context pack for Codex.
+- `sak ingest --repo owner/name` - create a source card without importing code directly.
+- `sak evidence add --standard nist-ssdf --detail "..."` - write proof into the ledger.
+- `sak screenshot --url data:text/html,...` - capture screenshot evidence or a placeholder if Playwright is missing.
+- `sak audit` - print the tool/source audit and court state.
+- `sak cron run` - run local watcher jobs and record evidence.
+- `sak court` - inspect blocked standards and release readiness.
+- `sak github sync` - sync the GitHub bridge if credentials are configured.
+- `sak mcp list`, `sak mcp get`, and `sak mcp search` - inspect the read-only local skill registry.
+- `sak mcp serve` - start the read-only stdio MCP bridge.
+- `sak benchmark run` - write a local blocked/partial benchmark snapshot.
+- `sak docker smoke` - validate Docker/Compose surfaces without starting containers.
+
+## Read-only API
+
+- `/api/state`
+- `/api/health`
+- `/api/db`
+- `/api/ledger`
+- `/api/evidence`
+- `/api/screenshots`
+- `/api/sources`
+- `/api/benchmark`
+- `/api/skills`
+- `/api/court`
+- `/api/tools`
+
+Write endpoint:
+
+- `POST /api/refresh`
+
+## One-click local app
+
+- `sak.cmd` is the repo-local command alias.
+- `launch.cmd` starts the deck from Windows Explorer.
+- `PALA_ROOT_DIR` can point the app at a different workspace root.
+- `PALA_OPEN_BROWSER=0` disables the browser launch during headless runs.
+
+## Local packaging
+
+- `.codex-plugin/plugin.json` defines a read-only stdio MCP surface with 4 tools.
+- `Dockerfile` boots the local dashboard with `node src/cli.js up`.
+- `compose.yaml` defines `pala-v6-dashboard` and `pala-v6-mcp` local services.
+- `docs/local-boot.md` records the honest boot constraints and remaining gaps.
+- `src/benchmark.js` provides a blocked/partial benchmark-state runner; it is not a fixture-backed benchmark suite yet.
+- `src/docker-smoke.js` records Docker/Compose smoke evidence without performing a deployment.
+
+## Health check
+
+Run `scripts/pala_codex_health.ps1` for a quick local wiring check.
+
+## Notes
+
+- The 60 standards are tracked in `.pala/rules/world-standards.json` and seeded into the local SQLite ledger during bootstrap.
+- Runtime databases, ledgers, screenshots, dashboard state, and raw evidence stay local and are ignored by Git.
+- The dashboard route changes based on local evidence, source cards, and blocker state.
+- External code is never imported directly. It must pass through a source card first.
+- OSS reference doctrine lives in `docs/oss-upstream-matrix.md`; OpenHands, UI/UX Pro Max, Continue, Cline, and Aider are treated as pattern sources, not blind dependencies.
