+# Codex Contract
+
+Codex works best here when it:
+- keeps patches small
+- loads only the needed files
+- writes evidence after each meaningful step
+- verifies with local commands before reporting success
+- treats Pala as the verifier layer, not the coder's brain
+
+## Preferred loop
+1. Read the current state with `sak status` or the dashboard.
+2. Request a context pack with `sak bak "<task>"`.
+3. Patch one layer at a time.
+4. Run the smallest proof command.
+5. Record evidence if the change matters.
+
+## Anti-patterns
+- loading the whole repo when only one module is needed
+- claiming pass without a test, command, or dashboard state
+- bypassing source cards for external code
+- mixing design work and risky implementation in one opaque step
