@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@
+# World Standards Map
+
+Pala OS V6 turns the V5 world-standard tabur into a machine-readable policy engine.
+
+## Status vocabulary
+- `required`: must have evidence to avoid a blocked state.
+- `recommended`: preferred, tracked, but not a hard stop.
+- `blocked`: required and currently missing evidence.
+- `not_applicable_with_reason`: outside the active focus for the current profile.
+
+## Evidence model
+Each standard can carry one or more evidence items:
+- command output
+- decision note
+- source card reference
+- GitHub issue / PR / commit reference
+- cron snapshot
+- security scan summary
+
+## First-pass families
+- NIST
+- OWASP
+- SLSA / OpenSSF / Sigstore / in-toto
+- SPDX / CycloneDX / VEX / GUAC
+- MITRE / CISA / CVSS
+- Docker / GitHub Actions / MCP
+- Pala operational law
+
+## How to use it
+1. Seed the catalog from `sak init`.
+2. Add evidence with `sak evidence add`.
+3. Inspect the dashboard or `sak status`.
+4. Run `sak cron run` to refresh watcher evidence.
+5. Open `sak court` whenever blocked standards stay unresolved.
